caption.text:
Simplified rock physics data of the rock types reviewed in this study. Note permeability data is not available for TB and EHB as this was not an important aim of the Harnett
89
study. In the case of NPS and COS, the anisotropy due to the bedding/fabric produces noticeable permeability anisotropy with typical low (normal to bedding) and high (parallel to bedding) values cited.
